OL,3,CCuts to mental health services
OL,4,C'putting lives at risk'
OL,6,FDr. John Mulligan, a clinical
OL,7,Fpsychologist, says action is essential
OL,8,Fnow to prevent more avoidable deaths
OL,9,Fin Greater Manchester.
OL,11,FWith a 60% above average need for
OL,12,Fmental health services in Manchester,
OL,13,Fstaff say a lack of investment is
OL,14,F"unsafe".
OL,16,FProfessor Anandi Ramamurthy, co-
OL,17,Ffounder of CHARM - a group for better
OL,18,Fholistic mental health services, says
OL,19,Fshe feels her daughter, who was
OL,20,Fdiagnosed with psychosis, was failed
OL,21,Fby the service when she was in need.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/9
