OL,3,CCuts to mental health services
OL,4,C'putting lives at risk'
OL,6,FIn a statement the Department of
OL,7,FHealth and Social Care said: "People
OL,8,Fwith mental health issues are not
OL,9,Fgetting the support or care they
OL,10,Fdeserve, which is why we will fix the
OL,11,Fbroken system to ensure we give mental
OL,12,Fhealth the same attention and focus as
OL,13,Fphysical health.
OL,15,F"We will start by recruiting 8,500
OL,16,Fmore mental health workers to cut
OL,17,Fwaits for treatment, and will also
OL,18,Freform the Mental Health Act, to
OL,19,Fensure people with the most severe
OL,20,Fmental health conditions get better,
OL,21,Fmore personalised care."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/9
